# HTML Advanced Forms Project

## 📌 Project Overview
This project demonstrates advanced HTML form concepts and techniques. It is designed to help learners understand how real-world forms work in modern websites, including validation, structured inputs, and better user experience design.

---

## 📚 What You Will Learn
In this project, you will learn:

- Advanced HTML form structure
- Form validation techniques
- Input types used in real websites:
  - Text, Email, Password
  - Number, Date, File upload
- Dropdown menus (Select & Option)
- Radio buttons and Checkboxes (advanced usage)
- Textarea for long messages
- Required fields and placeholders
- Basic form constraints (min, max, pattern)

---

## 🧪 Features of This Project
- Professional form layout structure
- User input validation using HTML attributes
- Organized and user-friendly design

- Real-world form examples (like registration/contact forms)
- Clean and readable code structure

